  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Checklist/important considerations:</h4>
  <ul class="dummy-list">
    <li>The element that serves as the container for the set of tabs has <code>role tablist</code>.</li>
    <li>Each element that serves as a tab has
      <code>role tab</code>
      and is contained within the element with
      <code>role tablist</code>.</li>
    <li>Each element that contains the content panel for a <code>tab</code> has <code>role tabpanel</code>.</li>
    <li>If the tab list has a visible label, the element with
      <code>role tablist</code>
      has
      <code>aria-labelledby</code>
      set to a value that refers to the labeling element. Otherwise, the
      <code>tablist</code>
      element has a label provided by
      <code>aria-label</code>.</li>
    <li>Each element with
      <code>role tab</code>
      has the property
      <code>aria-controls</code>
      referring to its associated
      <code>tabpanel</code>
      element.</li>
    <li>The active
      <code>tab</code>
      element has the state
      <code>aria-selected</code>
      set to
      <code>true</code>
      and all other
      <code>tab</code>
      elements have it set to
      <code>false</code>.</li>
    <li>Each element with
      <code>role tabpanel</code>
      has the attribute
      <code>aria-labelledby</code>
      referring to its associated
      <code>tab</code>
      element.</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Keyboard interactions</h4>
  <ul class="dummy-list">
    <li>
      <kbd>TAB</kbd>
      <ul>
        <li>When focus moves into the tab list, places focus on the active tab element.</li>
        <li>When the tab list contains the focus, moves focus to the next element in the page tab sequence. This could
          mean an interactive element inside of the active tabpanel, or the next interactive element on the page
          (outside of the tab element completely.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      When focus is on a tab element (assuming a horizontal tab list):
      <ul>
        <li><kbd>LEFT ARROW</kbd>: moves focus to the previous tab. If focus is on the first tab, moves focus to the
          last tab.</li>
        <li><kbd>RIGHT ARROW</kbd>: Moves focus to the next tab. If focus is on the last tab element, moves focus to the
          first tab.</li>
        <li><kbd>SPACE</kbd> or <kbd>ENTER</kbd>: Activates the tab (to display the tabpanel content)</li>
        <li>
          Optional features:
          <ul>
            <li><kbd>HOME</kbd>: Moves focus to the first tab element in the tab list</li>
            <li><kbd>END</kbd>: Moves focus to the last tab element in the tab list</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

